    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but is it even a \"debate\" anymore though? like, most mainstream economists say tariffs are just bad, but that feels like they're just ignoring the reality of national security and needing to be self-sufficient. if we rely entirely on other countries for everything, we're vulnerable. isn't it basically a fact that being too reliant on global trade is a strategic mistake for a nation, regardless of what the \"efficiency\" models say?",
