      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The argument for national resilience and supply chain security is increasingly influential, moving beyond pure efficiency models. Many voices now argue that dependency on foreign powers for critical goods presents a fundamental national security risk, a concept that economics alone often fails to quantify. Therefore, what was once seen strictly as an economic debate is now merging with geopolitical strategy. This recognition is shifting the conversation toward \"reshoring\" and strategic trade policy rather than just cost reduction.",
      "source": "target",
